Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.12,0:02:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,32 ok)\NRed Horse in the Fire\NPart 2
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tell you, what the hell is that fool doing anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.73,0:02:32.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought him a t-shirt that I thought would look good on him and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.50,0:02:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come, come, they'll be home soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.93,0:02:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this key holder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.40,0:02:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, a kindly looking old man gave it us on the bus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.54,0:02:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh the man who gave us his seat saying that we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.91,0:02:48.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,looked to be carrying a heavy load...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.28,0:02:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you so very much
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.51,0:02:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.08,0:02:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Uh, where are you girls living?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to pick us up, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.05,0:02:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.39,0:03:01.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,NN. No. I run an antique shop at Haidocho...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.13,0:03:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I thought I'd like you to drop in one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.13,0:03:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haidocho is nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.26,0:03:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My house is right next to it on Beikacho 5-chome
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.13,0:03:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh,. 5 chome...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.80,0:03:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we go tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.77,0:03:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll give you the catalog of my shop and a key holder...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.14,0:03:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Promise, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.68,0:03:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what a key holder
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.01,0:03:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that brings flourishing business is all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.75,0:03:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go, Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.62,0:03:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The four red horses... that were found at the serial arson sites!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.44,0:03:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went way out to ask the forensic officers for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.23,0:03:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you'd better find some sort of a clue, or you're going to get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:43.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not the one who want to see the horses, they do...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.57,0:03:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come... only this horse from the first fire 1s burnt black like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.80,0:03:50.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And only this horse has a stand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.41,0:03:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? There's something written on the back of the stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.01,0:03:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey... A red horse and rabbit...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.68,0:04:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D:Donrt tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:03.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't this... Kanu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.82,0:04:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kanuyis the military commander who appears in the story Sangokusht, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.92,0:04:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kanu is also famous for being the god of prosperity for doing business
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.33,0:04:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what a flashy colored horse he's riding
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.63,0:04:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a "Sekitouba (Red Rabbit Horse)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a super horse said to be able to run a thousand miles in a day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.97,0:04:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Red Rabbit Horse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.71,0:04:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that this red plastic horse is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.78,0:04:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a famous horse that appears in Sagokushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.58,0:04:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try looking at the stand of this horse that was left at the first scene of the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.18,0:04:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You-can't read the words above and under it because they re burnt,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.45,0:04:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you can see the word rabbit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.72,0:04:43.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, true...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only red horse with the word rabbit to its name is the horse
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that ran around battlefields\NWI 1S VICIOUS MI I ary comman er
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on its back, Red Rabbit Horse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.97,0:04:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did the arsonist put the legendary horse that appears in an old Chinese story
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.50,0:04:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at the sites he set fire to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.77,0:04:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.64,0:05:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,China...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.74,0:05:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,China...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.01,0:05:04.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Feng Shui is also from China, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who came to the\NMorozumi residence before the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.62,0:05:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,didn't he say anything to Ryoko about the old Chinese story?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.72,0:05:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't say anything about Sangokushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.26,0:05:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but that Sensei of Feng Shui's got a perfect motive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.23,0:05:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.26,0:05:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was looking for the video tape of his affair
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.87,0:05:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with Ryoko Morozumi who died in the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can'tâ¢be!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.74,0:05:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get rid of the video tape he burned down the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.81,0:05:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yuminaga!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.71,0:05:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.78,0:05:41.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! If you find out anything more, please report to me again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.72,0:05:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes sir
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the ones with motive is not limited to that Sensei
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.99,0:05:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keiko Gondo, the fortune-teller that came to the house before the Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.00,0:05:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems that she's going to get a large sum
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.25,0:06:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of estate from her parents being that she's oko's older-sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.94,0:06:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it that fortuneteller-was saying that their father just died!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that lady came to borrow money from Ryoko
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.15,0:06:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she was going to inherit the estate of her father anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.75,0:06:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why would she do something like that...
